{"parse":{"title":"Esol Education","pageid":5360975,"revid":853669466,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\">See also: <a href=\"/wiki/English_as_a_foreign_or_second_language\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"English as a foreign or second language\">English as a foreign or second language</a></div>\n<table class=\"plainlinks metadata ambox ambox-content ambox-Primary_sources\" role=\"presentation\"><tbody><tr><td class=\"mbox-image\"><div style=\"width:52px\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Question_book-new.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Question book-new.svg\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/50px-Question_book-new.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"39\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/75px-Question_book-new.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/100px-Question_book-new.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"512\" data-file-height=\"399\" /></a></div></td><td class=\"mbox-text\"><div class=\"mbox-text-span\">This article <b>relies too much on <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Verifiability\" title=\"Wikipedia:Verifiability\">references</a> to <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:No_original_research#Primary,_secondary_and_tertiary_sources\" title=\"Wikipedia:No original research\">primary sources</a></b>.<span class=\"hide-when-compact\"> Please improve this  by adding <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:No_original_research#Primary,_secondary_and_tertiary_sources\" title=\"Wikipedia:No original research\">secondary or tertiary sources</a>.</span>  <small><i>(June 2015)</i></small><small class=\"hide-when-compact\"><i> (<a href=\"/wiki/Help:Maintenance_template_removal\" title=\"Help:Maintenance template removal\">Learn how and when to remove this template message</a>)</i></small></div></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<table class=\"infobox vcard\" style=\"width:22em\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" class=\"fn org\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;background-color: lavender\">Esol Education</th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/File:Esol_Education_Logo.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Esol Education Logo.jpg\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/a/af/Esol_Education_Logo.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"118\" data-file-width=\"220\" data-file-height=\"118\" /></a></td></tr><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;background:lavender\">Location</th></tr><tr class=\"adr\"><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<span class=\"locality\"><span class=\"flagicon\"><a href=\"/wiki/United_Arab_Emirates\" title=\"United Arab Emirates\"><img alt=\"United Arab Emirates\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/cb/Flag_of_the_United_Arab_Emirates.svg/23px-Flag_of_the_United_Arab_Emirates.svg.png\" width=\"23\" height=\"12\" class=\"thumbborder\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/cb/Flag_of_the_United_Arab_Emirates.svg/35px-Flag_of_the_United_Arab_Emirates.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/cb/Flag_of_the_United_Arab_Emirates.svg/46px-Flag_of_the_United_Arab_Emirates.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"1200\" data-file-height=\"600\" /></a></span> - <span class=\"flagicon\"><a href=\"/wiki/Hong_Kong\" title=\"Hong Kong\"><img alt=\"Hong Kong\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/5b/Flag_of_Hong_Kong.svg/23px-Flag_of_Hong_Kong.svg.png\" width=\"23\" height=\"15\" class=\"thumbborder\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/5b/Flag_of_Hong_Kong.svg/35px-Flag_of_Hong_Kong.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/5b/Flag_of_Hong_Kong.svg/45px-Flag_of_Hong_Kong.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"900\" data-file-height=\"600\" /></a></span> - <span class=\"flagicon\"><a href=\"/wiki/Egypt\" title=\"Egypt\"><img alt=\"Egypt\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fe/Flag_of_Egypt.svg/23px-Flag_of_Egypt.svg.png\" width=\"23\" height=\"15\" class=\"thumbborder\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fe/Flag_of_Egypt.svg/35px-Flag_of_Egypt.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fe/Flag_of_Egypt.svg/45px-Flag_of_Egypt.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"900\" data-file-height=\"600\" /></a></span> - <span class=\"flagicon\"><a href=\"/wiki/Cyprus\" title=\"Cyprus\"><img alt=\"Cyprus\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d4/Flag_of_Cyprus.svg/23px-Flag_of_Cyprus.svg.png\" width=\"23\" height=\"15\" class=\"thumbborder\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d4/Flag_of_Cyprus.svg/35px-Flag_of_Cyprus.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d4/Flag_of_Cyprus.svg/45px-Flag_of_Cyprus.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"900\" data-file-height=\"600\" /></a></span> - <span class=\"flagicon\"><a href=\"/wiki/Lebanon\" title=\"Lebanon\"><img alt=\"Lebanon\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/59/Flag_of_Lebanon.svg/23px-Flag_of_Lebanon.svg.png\" width=\"23\" height=\"15\" class=\"thumbborder\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/59/Flag_of_Lebanon.svg/35px-Flag_of_Lebanon.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/59/Flag_of_Lebanon.svg/45px-Flag_of_Lebanon.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"750\" data-file-height=\"500\" /></a></span></span><br /><span class=\"country-name\"><a href=\"/wiki/UAE\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"UAE\">UAE</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Hong_Kong\" title=\"Hong Kong\">Hong Kong</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Egypt\" title=\"Egypt\">Egypt</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Cyprus\" title=\"Cyprus\">Cyprus</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Lebanon\" title=\"Lebanon\">Lebanon</a></span></td></tr><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;background:lavender\">Information</th></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Type</th><td>\nAmerican and British <a href=\"/wiki/International_school\" title=\"International school\">international schools</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Founded</th><td>\n1976<span class=\"noprint\">&#59;&#32;42&#160;years ago</span><span style=\"display:none\">&#160;(<span class=\"bday dtstart published updated\">1976</span>)</span></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Founder</th><td>\nWalid Abushakra</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Accreditation</th><td>\nMiddle States Associations of Colleges and School, MSA Council of International Schools, CIS</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Website</th><td class=\"plainlinks\">\n<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.esoleducation.com\"><b>www.esoleducation.com</b></a></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:152px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Walid_Abushakra.JPG\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/bb/Walid_Abushakra.JPG/150px-Walid_Abushakra.JPG\" width=\"150\" height=\"225\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/bb/Walid_Abushakra.JPG/225px-Walid_Abushakra.JPG 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/bb/Walid_Abushakra.JPG/300px-Walid_Abushakra.JPG 2x\" data-file-width=\"3840\" data-file-height=\"5760\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Walid_Abushakra.JPG\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Walid Abushakra, the Chairman of Esol Education</div></div></div>\n<p>The organization announced in 2017 that it will establish three new schools: Dunecrest American School in Dubai (opening 2018), Fairgreen International School in Dubai (opening 2018) and American International School in Bahrain (opening in 2019).\n</p><p><b>Esol Education</b> (formerly knows as ESOL - Educational Services Overseas Limited), is an organization in the field of <a href=\"/wiki/Primary_education\" title=\"Primary education\">primary</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Secondary_education\" title=\"Secondary education\">secondary education</a>, specialized in establishing and managing American and British <a href=\"/wiki/International_school\" title=\"International school\">international schools</a>. Esol Education currently owns and operates 9 schools.\n</p>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/American_International_School,_Abu_Dhabi\" title=\"American International School, Abu Dhabi\">American International School in Abu Dhabi, AISA</a></li>\n<li>Dunecrest American School, Dubai</li>\n<li>Fairgreen International School, Dubai</li>\n<li>American School Hong Kong</li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/The_American_International_School_in_Egypt\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"The American International School in Egypt\">The American International School in Egypt - Main, AISEM</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/The_American_International_School_in_Egypt\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"The American International School in Egypt\">The American International School in Egypt - West, AISEW</a></li>\n<li>Cairo English School</li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/The_American_International_School_in_Cyprus\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"The American International School in Cyprus\">American International School in Cyprus, AISC</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/The_Universal_College_in_Aley\" title=\"The Universal College in Aley\">Universal College - Aley, UCA</a></li></ul>\n<p>Across its schools, Esol Education has a total enrollment of close to 10,000 students.\n7,000+ enrollment in UAE with 1,000+ teachers 4 Schools and more new to come\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Leadership\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Leadership</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Schools\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Schools</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#United_Arab_Emirates\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">United Arab Emirates</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#American_International_School_in_Abu_Dhabi_(AISA)\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">American International School in Abu Dhabi (AISA)</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Dunecrest_American_School,_Dubai_(Dunecrest)\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Dunecrest American School, Dubai (Dunecrest)</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#Fairgreen_International_School,_Dubai_(Fairgreen)\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Fairgreen International School, Dubai (Fairgreen)</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#Egypt\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Egypt</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-8\"><a href=\"#American_International_School_in_Egypt_-_Main_(AISEM)\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">American International School in Egypt - Main (AISEM)</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-9\"><a href=\"#American_International_School_in_Egypt_-_West_(AISEW)\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">American International School in Egypt - West (AISEW)</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-10\"><a href=\"#Cairo_English_School_(CES)\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4.3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Cairo English School (CES)</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-11\"><a href=\"#Cyprus\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Cyprus</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-12\"><a href=\"#American_International_School_in_Cyprus_(AISC)\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">American International School in Cyprus (AISC)</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-13\"><a href=\"#Lebanon\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Lebanon</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-14\"><a href=\"#Universal_College\u2014Aley_(UCA)\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Universal College\u2014Aley (UCA)</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-15\"><a href=\"#Gallery\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">7</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Gallery</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-16\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">8</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Leadership\">Leadership</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Esol_Education&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Leadership\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Esol Education was founded by Walid Abushakra.\n</p><p>Mr. Abushakra was joined by his sons, Tammam Abushakra and Bassam Abushakra, who oversee the operations of the company.  They are supported by a leadership team composed of educators from leading school bodies and education councils around the world.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Schools\">Schools</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Esol_Education&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Schools\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The American International School in Egypt (AISE) was established in 1990. Soon thereafter, Esol Education assumed operation of the American International School in Cyprus (AISC) and founded the American International School in Abu Dhabi (AISA) in 1995. The organization also established and operated a number of small schools in Saudi Arabia during this period.\n</p><p>The Universal College in Aley, Lebanon (UCA) joined the fold in 2000, with ESOL restoring its war-damaged campus and reopening the historic school for the first time since the Lebanese Civil War had forced its closure in 1982. Around the same time, ESOL participated in the establishment of the American International School in Gaza (AISG).\n</p><p>In 2005, ESOL\u2019s success with AISA opened the opportunity in the United Arab Emirates as the doors of its first two schools in <a href=\"/wiki/Dubai\" title=\"Dubai\">Dubai</a> opened, the Universal American School in Dubai (UAS) and the Deira International School (DIS). The opening of the Cairo English School followed in 2006, and AISE's West Campus opened in 2009 in the Cairo's western suburbs. Most recently in 2013, ESOL assumed the ownership and management of Inspire Children\u2019s Nursery in Dubai, which marks ESOL Education\u2019s first venture into the growing early education sector.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"United_Arab_Emirates\">United Arab Emirates</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Esol_Education&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: United Arab Emirates\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span id=\"American_International_School_in_Abu_Dhabi_.28AISA.29\"></span><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"American_International_School_in_Abu_Dhabi_(AISA)\">American International School in Abu Dhabi (AISA)</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Esol_Education&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: American International School in Abu Dhabi (AISA)\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>AISA was the first school in <a href=\"/wiki/Abu_Dhabi\" title=\"Abu Dhabi\">Abu Dhabi</a> to be authorized to offer the <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.ibo.org/school/000895/\">International Baccalaureate Diploma Program (IB DP)</a> and the first to be authorized to offer the IB Primary Years Program (IBPYP).\n</p>\n<h3><span id=\"Dunecrest_American_School.2C_Dubai_.28Dunecrest.29\"></span><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Dunecrest_American_School,_Dubai_(Dunecrest)\">Dunecrest American School, Dubai (Dunecrest)</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Esol_Education&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: Dunecrest American School, Dubai (Dunecrest)\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Located at the Al Barari/Living Legends, Dunecrest American School will be opening in September 2018.  \n</p>\n<h3><span id=\"Fairgreen_International_School.2C_Dubai_.28Fairgreen.29\"></span><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Fairgreen_International_School,_Dubai_(Fairgreen)\">Fairgreen International School, Dubai (Fairgreen)</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Esol_Education&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" title=\"Edit section: Fairgreen International School, Dubai (Fairgreen)\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Opening in 2018. Fairgreen International School is <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://gulfnews.com/xpress/news/now-a-school-with-farms-food-lab-health-biodome-1.2100548\">Dubai's first sustainability-focused school.</a> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external autonumber\" href=\"https://www.khaleejtimes.com/news/education/dubai-to-get-its-first-sustainable-school\">[1]</a> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external autonumber\" href=\"https://whichschooladvisor.com/uae/school-review/fairgreen-international-school\">[2]</a> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external autonumber\" href=\"https://schoolscompared.com/all-through/dubai-all-through/fairgreen-international-school-sustainable-city-dubailand/\">[3]</a>\n</p><p>The Fairgreen campus will be powered by renewable energy, recycle all its water for agricultural use, implements waste separation and wind energy generation. The school's approach to learning will focus on environmental, community and economic sustainability. \n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Egypt\">Egypt</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Esol_Education&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" title=\"Edit section: Egypt\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span id=\"American_International_School_in_Egypt_-_Main_.28AISEM.29\"></span><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"American_International_School_in_Egypt_-_Main_(AISEM)\">American International School in Egypt - Main (AISEM)</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Esol_Education&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8\" title=\"Edit section: American International School in Egypt - Main (AISEM)\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>The American International School in Egypt opened its doors to its first 240 students in 1990. Today, AIS Egypt has two campuses, with a combined student population of over 2000 students. \n</p>\n<h3><span id=\"American_International_School_in_Egypt_-_West_.28AISEW.29\"></span><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"American_International_School_in_Egypt_-_West_(AISEW)\">American International School in Egypt - West (AISEW)</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Esol_Education&amp;action=edit&amp;section=9\" title=\"Edit section: American International School in Egypt - West (AISEW)\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Inaugurated under the Pyramids in August 2009, AISEW serves the local and international community in Cairo.\n</p>\n<h3><span id=\"Cairo_English_School_.28CES.29\"></span><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Cairo_English_School_(CES)\">Cairo English School (CES)</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Esol_Education&amp;action=edit&amp;section=10\" title=\"Edit section: Cairo English School (CES)\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>CES provides British based international education and also delivers a tailored curriculum, offering Arabic, Egyptian Social Studies and Religion to its Egyptian students.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Cyprus\">Cyprus</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Esol_Education&amp;action=edit&amp;section=11\" title=\"Edit section: Cyprus\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span id=\"American_International_School_in_Cyprus_.28AISC.29\"></span><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"American_International_School_in_Cyprus_(AISC)\">American International School in Cyprus (AISC)</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Esol_Education&amp;action=edit&amp;section=12\" title=\"Edit section: American International School in Cyprus (AISC)\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Situated on a 16,000 m<sup>2</sup> area of Nicosia.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Lebanon\">Lebanon</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Esol_Education&amp;action=edit&amp;section=13\" title=\"Edit section: Lebanon\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span id=\"Universal_College.E2.80.94Aley_.28UCA.29\"></span><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Universal_College\u2014Aley_(UCA)\">Universal College\u2014Aley (UCA)</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Esol_Education&amp;action=edit&amp;section=14\" title=\"Edit section: Universal College\u2014Aley (UCA)\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>UCA is a college preparatory school in <a href=\"/wiki/Aley\" title=\"Aley\">Aley</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Lebanon\" title=\"Lebanon\">Lebanon</a>. It is located above <a href=\"/wiki/Beirut\" title=\"Beirut\">Beirut</a> on <a href=\"/wiki/Mount_Lebanon\" title=\"Mount Lebanon\">Mount Lebanon</a>. It is approved to operate by the Lebanese Ministry of Education, offering the Lebanese Baccalaureate and/or American Diploma. UCA was reopened in 2000.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Gallery\">Gallery</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Esol_Education&amp;action=edit&amp;section=15\" title=\"Edit section: Gallery\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul class=\"gallery mw-gallery-packed-hover\">\n\t\t<li class=\"gallerybox\" style=\"width: 186.66666666667px\"><div style=\"width: 186.66666666667px\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"thumb\" style=\"width: 184.66666666667px;\"><div style=\"margin:0px auto;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:AISA_Front_Facade.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/74/AISA_Front_Facade.jpg/277px-AISA_Front_Facade.jpg\" width=\"185\" height=\"120\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/74/AISA_Front_Facade.jpg/415px-AISA_Front_Facade.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/74/AISA_Front_Facade.jpg/553px-AISA_Front_Facade.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"2448\" data-file-height=\"1594\" /></a></div></div>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"gallerytextwrapper\" style=\"width